Former Deputy Governor of the Central Bank of Nigeria (CBN) and presidential candidate in the 2019 elections, Prof. Kingsley Chiedu Moghalu, has been conferred with the Nnewi traditional chieftaincy title of ‘Ifek’ego Nnewi’ (that which is greater than money) by the Igwe of Nnewi, Dr Kenneth Orizu III.
 
The title was conferred by the monarch of the 600-year-old hereditary kingdom at a colourful ceremony in Nnewi during Igwe Orizu’s 57th annual Ofala festival held on December 28.  To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .